HEADWORD: nonvocalic
<hw>nonvocalic</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Phonology)</fld> <def>not
vocalic; not having vowel character; -- used of liquids and nasals.
Opposite of <ant>vocalic</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> consonantal, nonsyllabic.</syn>⟦br⟧
